Hungarian June Gross Wages Rise at Slowest Rate in Three Months

-- B y   A n d r a s   G e r g e l y
-- 
2011-08-19T07:00:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-19/hungarian-june-gross-wages-rise-at-slowest-rate-in-three-months.html
Hungarian wages rose in June at the
slowest rate in three months, the Budapest-based statistics
office said in a statement today.  The average monthly gross wage increased 4.7 percent from a
year earlier to 212,168 forint ($1,111), the office said. The
median estimate of 10 economists in a Bloomberg survey was 4.8
percent. Wages advanced 6.7 percent in May.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Andras Gergely in Budapest at 
 agergely@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Gavin Serkin at 
 gserkin@bloomberg.net  